cuisine: Middle East
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tomato-shakshuka-with-feta-646463f800cc5c0d220c0f65
---

Bring @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) to room temperature. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(half); finely dice remaining onion. Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, @red wine vinegar{5%tsp}, 1 tsp @sugar{1.25%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings), @salt{} and @pepper{}. Microwave for ~{30%seconds}; set aside to pickle.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a medium pan (large pan for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add diced onion, bell pepper, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @chili powder{1%tsp} and half the @garlic powder{1%tsp} (you'll use the rest in Step 5); cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce}, @veggie stock concentrate{2}, and ¼ tsp sugar (½ tsp for 4 servings); cook, stirring, until reduced and jammy, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir @water{1/3%cup} (½ cup for 4) into same pan; bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture has thickened and veggies have softened, ~{3-5%minutes}. (TIP: Add another splash of water if veggies need more time to soften.) Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, in a second #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, and remaining garlic powder. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Reduce heat under pan with tomato sauce to medium. Using the back of a #ladle{} or #spoon{}, make four wells (eight wells for 4 servings) in tomato sauce. Carefully crack an @eggs{4} into each well. Cover pan and cook until egg whites are set and yolks are cooked to preference. Lightly season with salt and pepper.

While eggs cook, toast @whole wheat pitas{2}, then spread with softened butter. Quarter pitas.

Sprinkle shakshuka with @feta cheese{1/2%cup} and top with pickled onion (draining first). Drizzle with garlic sauce and garnish with parsley.

Serve family style directly from pan, with pita wedges on the side.

> Wash hands and surfaces after handling raw eggs. Consuming raw or undercooked eggs may increase your risk of foodborne illness.